### 3.2 Exact indexed `K/E/Pi` block to extract

The recovered absolute block is

```text
dK/dm = -K/(2m) + E/(2m(1-m))
dE/dm = -K/(2m) + E/(2m)
```

over `Q(m)`, with singular support `m=0,1,infinity`. For the complementary
pair `K~=K(1-m)`, `E~=E(1-m)`, the exact constant bilinear invariant is

```text
B = E K~ + E~ K - K K~,       dB/dm = 0.
```

Entry `E-0022` additionally supplies the selected family

```text
m(s) = A(s) = 1/2 - 1/(2 sqrt(1+s^2))
C(s) = (sqrt(1+s^2)-1)/(sqrt(1+s^2)+1)
n(s) = (A(s)-C(s))/(1-C(s))
L(s) = 2 g(s) [Pi(n(s);m(s))-(1-C(s))K(m(s))].
```

Entry `E-0014` supplies the fixed primary/dual DBP `K/Pi` normal forms and the
regular dual CPV rewrite. The live `engine/src/cella/periods.py` already records
exact quartics, residues, structural basis coefficients, the regular identity
`CPV Pi(n;m)=K(m)-Pi(m/n;m)`, and exact basis differences.

Together these constrain the target to the finite span selected by the DBP
family. They do not themselves prove its parameter connection or its matching
to the integral relative-homology basis.

