### 5.2 Selection theorem to extract

On

```text
Cham = {4M > sum_i |N_i|},
```

the existing R5 package proves that every mass-square root is positive and
real, each positive-imbalance sheet crosses once and transversely, and the
all-plus root is the unique least root. It also gives

```text
u_phys = lambda_max(L_0^(-1/2) Z L_0^(-1/2))^(-2).
```

For `k=4` with pairwise distinct `N_i^2`, all five roots are simple
throughout the strict chamber. Uniqueness plus simplicity gives an analytic
physical section fixed by continuation along loops wholly contained in that
chamber. This closes the mathematical selection rule for that domain.

Therefore `PhysicalSelectionUnproved` is not an accurate blocker for the
strict static chamber. It remains accurate only outside the theorem-owned
domain, including rotating/indefinite or unproved wall-crossing routes.

